715033f-a.text:
West 110th Street, at Eighth Avenue (right), and westward,
showing thereupon the curved "El" trestle of the Sixth and
Ninth Avenue's Elevated Line. At the left, this structure
veers southward to continue on Columbus Avenue. The hilly
ground beyond is the Morningside Heights section, that will
later contain the Cathedral of St. John and Morningside Park.
The photographers vantage point is upon the thoroughfare
that became Central Park West after development.

About 1882

Gift of
Collection of George T. Bagoe
No. 86 Madison Avenue, N. Y. C.
NEG #1548
